cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DM

This paper is about a machine learning method called tree boosting, which is commonly used in various applications such as computer vision and data mining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of tree boosting in computer vision (e.g., image classification), which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another possible category. Finally, the paper mentions data compression and sharding, which are relevant to cs.DM (Data Management).
